In the Czech Republic, tax payers must submit their VAT returns no later than 25 days after the end of the tax period.
Depending on the turnover of the taxable person, the tax period is either the calendar quarter or the calendar month.
In Germany, depending on the amount of their tax liability in the previous year, the tax payers have to file their advance applications no later than 10 days after either the end of the calendar quarter or the calendar month.
The annual sales tax declaration must be made by 31 May of the following year at the latest.
The plan to issue an annual sales tax return has some advantages and disadvantages:
+ After the end of the calendar year, the taxable person can correct the errors in the monthly advance registrations by submitting a single VAT return;
- if the taxpayer corrects his information on intra-Community transactions, the correction cannot be attributed to a specific reporting period of the ZM;
